channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: IRONY: On Day He Was Supposed to Be Sentenced, Trump Files Motion to Have His NY Convictions Thrown Out
'Record' fundraising haul by GOP Senate candidate in blue-leaning southwest state
item.description: Republican Senate nominee Nella Domenici reports hauling in $2.9 million during the April-June second quarter of 2024 fundraising, a record for a U.S. Senate candidate in New Mexico.

item.title: Biden Faces More Pressure From Democrats to Abandon Reelection Bid
item.description: President Joe Biden faced more calls from fellow Democrats to abandon his reelection bid on Friday, following a news conference in which he delivered nuanced responses but occasionally stumbled over his words.It was unclear whether Biden's performance would convince...

item.title: My How Time Flies: Twenty Years of RedState
GOP plans major crackdown on 'nameless, faceless bureaucrats' after blockbuster Supreme Court ruling
item.description: In the wake of the Supreme Court decision that cut the legs out from federal agencies, GOP lawmakers are launching a new effort to snatch even more power from the "administrative state."

item.title: Kremlin: Whole World Paid Attention to Biden's NATO Summit Gaffes
item.description: The Kremlin said on Friday that the whole world had paid attention to U.S. President Joe Biden's slips of the tongue at a NATO summit a day earlier, but said it was for U.S. voters, not Russia, to determine the U.S. presidential candidates' prospects. The Kremlin was...

item.title: The Bleeding Won't Stop: Biden Insiders Reportedly Melting Down, See 'No Path to Victory'
FLASHBACK: Ex-Dem lawmaker supporting Biden invoked his dad’s age in 2019 attack on Biden’s stamina
item.description: CNN contributor Bakari Sellers suggested President Biden was too old to serve as president in 2019 before donating to his campaign in 2024 and defending his age.

item.title: Grenell to Newsmax: 'Shameful' Biden Overshadowed NATO Week
item.description: Richard Grenell, former acting director of national intelligence, told Newsmax on Thursday it's shameful that the spotlight was redirected from NATO to "incompetent" President Joe Biden this week with all of the hot spots around the globe.

item.title: Biden Claimed in His 'Big Boy Presser' That Only He Could Beat Trump; DDHQ Issued the Real Receipts
Tester denies tight race, says internal polling has him beating Sheehy: ’Kicking his a--’
item.description: Sen. Jon Tester dismissed the idea that his Senate race in Montana is competitive, claiming he was handily defeating his Republican opponent in internal polls.

item.title: Biden: Ukraine Can't Use US Weapons to Hit Deep Inside Russia
item.description: President Joe Biden on Thursday rejected calls by Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy to lift restrictions and to allow Kyiv to use U.S. weapons to strike targets deep inside Russia.

item.title: 'Absolutely Priceless': The Looks on the Faces of the Biden Team When Joe Confuses Kamala and Trump
Biden says 'anyway' at least 9 times while trailing off in press conference
item.description: President Biden used the word "anyway" at least nine times while trailing off on a thought during his high-stakes press conference Thursday evening.

item.title: Karl Rove Endorses N.D. Gov. Burgum for VP
item.description: Republican strategist Karl Rove on Thursday endorsed North Dakota Gov. Doug Burgum to be former President Donald Trump's running mate.
